Docker logs: docker logs -f <container-is>

Build image: docker build -t <Image-Name> .

Remove image: docker image rm -f <Image-Name>

Docker save myimage:latest | gzip > myimage_latest.tar.gz

Run in port: docker run -it -d -p 8080:80 <Image-Name>

Tagging Docker Image: docker tag Image YOUR_DOCKERHUB_NAME/Image

Pushing to hub: docker push YOUR_DOCKERHUB_NAME/firstimage

Remove all stopped containers: docker container prune

docker-compose down

docker-compose up -d

docker exec -it <container-is> sh -->run curl then

docker volume create my-vol


